\": 599}, {\"ngram\": \"hours\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"the evening\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"little time\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 677}, {\"ngram\": \"recovery\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 690}, {\"ngram\": \"Adeleke\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 705}, {\"ngram\": \"her fastest leg\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 728}, {\"ngram\": \"the weekend\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having received the baton in fourth, she powered Ireland into second place before Femke Bol pipped Sharlene Mawdsley on the home straight asIreland claimed bronze and a national record.\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 828, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999959300112, \"rank\": 3.638917326227469e-09, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Femke Bol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the baton\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 804}, {\"ngram\": \"second place\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"Sharlene Mawdsley\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"the home\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"straight asIreland\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 941}, {\"ngram\": \"a national record\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 963}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A first senior championship medal for Adeleke, and another reminder of her importance to Team Ireland; her blistering leg was over a second faster than any other female runner in the event.\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 1155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1055, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.953516830798728e-18, \"text\": \"Team Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_at_the_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adeleke\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1011}, {\"ngram\": \"her importance\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"her blistering leg\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"any other female runner\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Was she surprised just how fast she could go given the unforgiving schedule?\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1233, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the unforgiving schedule\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Kind of, but my coach wasn't surprised at all,\\\" she tells RT\\u00c9 Sport fresh from her graduation from the University of Texas.\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1359, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my coach\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"RT\\u00c9 Sport\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"her graduation\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"Texas\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I surprised myself, to see how strong I was.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each round I was getting faster.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1441, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was able to get out (in the final), hold it the whole way and continue to catch people.\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was a testament to how my training has been going.\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1589, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a testament\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1554}, {\"ngram\": \"my training\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1573}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not until you race you can really see it translate to the race.\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1657}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That made me really excited for the rest of the season.\\\"\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1715, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"the season\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The demands on Adeleke are obvious.\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1752, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The demands\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1728}, {\"ngram\": \"Adeleke\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She sat out the women's 4x400m final with a spot in Paris already secured, but choosing what events to plump for, at both the European Championships in Rome next month as well as the Olympics, will come down to her coach Edrick Flor\\u00e9al.\", \"from\": 1753, \"to\": 1989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1805, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.7147695872353015e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9981329759355113, \"rank\": 0.0018674823241907983, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 1974, \"end\": 1988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edrick_Flor\\u00e9al\", \"score\": 0.9999999992505764, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Edrick Flor\\u00e9al\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edrick_Flor\\u00e9al\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edrick_Flor\\u00e9al\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the women's 4x400m\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"a spot\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"what events\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"both the European Championships\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"her coach\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1973}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sonia O'Sullivan has spoken that Adeleke will have to make big decisions this summer to get the best out of herself as an individual - \\\"that's what the best athletes do - they decide what's best for them\\\" but the athlete herself says that will come closer to the events themselves.\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1991, \"end\": 2007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sonia_O'Sullivan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sonia O'Sullivan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sonia_O'Sullivan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sonia_O'Sullivan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adeleke\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2031}, {\"ngram\": \"big decisions\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2123}, {\"ngram\": \"the best athletes\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2156}, {\"ngram\": \"the athlete\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2211}, {\"ngram\": \"the events\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Rome, the 400m heats are on the morning after the mixed relay final, while in Paris, the mixed relay heats and final are on the opening day of the athletics.\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2277, \"end\": 2281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9981329759355113, \"rank\": 0.0018674823241907983, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 2355, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.7147695872353015e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 400m heats\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2297}, {\"ngram\": \"the morning\", \"from\": 2305, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"the mixed relay\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2338}, {\"ngram\": \"the mixed relay\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening day\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2416}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletics\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adeleke says she could well compete in the 200m instead of the 400m at the Europeans to conserve energy ahead of the showpiece in August - \\\"the goal at the Europeans is to win gold, it's about the event that requires the least energy consumption\\\" - but will place all her faith regarding her events in the hands of Floreal.\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2759, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adeleke\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2443}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200m\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2483}, {\"ngram\": \"the Europeans\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2520}, {\"ngram\": \"energy\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2539}, {\"ngram\": \"the showpiece\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2562}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2572}, {\"ngram\": \"the goal\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2584}, {\"ngram\": \"the Europeans\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2601}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2612, \"to\": 2616}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2638}, {\"ngram\": \"the least energy consumption\", \"from\": 2653, \"to\": 2681}, {\"ngram\": \"all her faith\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2713}, {\"ngram\": \"her events\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2734}, {\"ngram\": \"the hands\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2747}, {\"ngram\": \"Floreal\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2758}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Honestly, it really just depends on what my coach says,\\\" she says.\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2828, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my coach\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If he wants me to run the relays, I will run the relays.\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2886, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the relays\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2862}, {\"ngram\": \"the relays\", \"from\": 2875, \"to\": 2885}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's all down to him as he is very experienced.\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 2934, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He knows my training, what I can do, what my fitness is looking like.\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 3004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my training\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"my fitness\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If he thinks it is something that is possible, I'd love to do the relays, because I'd love to win a relay medal with my team.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3035}, {\"ngram\": \"the relays\", \"from\": 3069, \"to\": 3079}, {\"ngram\": \"a relay medal\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3118}, {\"ngram\": \"my team\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But if he thinks it will not allow me to do what I should be able to do in an individual event, it will have to be that way.\\\"\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an individual event\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3227}, {\"ngram\": \"that way\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the past three global finals that Ireland has contested, the result was eighth place in the mixed relay, and a sixth place in the women's 4x400m that could have been bronze with Adeleke on the team.\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3461, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3297, \"end\": 3304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999959300112, \"rank\": 3.638917326227469e-09, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the past three global finals\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 3320, \"to\": 3330}, {\"ngram\": \"eighth place\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3347}, {\"ngram\": \"the mixed relay\", \"from\": 3351, \"to\": 3366}, {\"ngram\": \"a sixth place\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3385}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3435}, {\"ngram\": \"Adeleke\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3448}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 3452, \"to\": 3460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has spoken about Ireland's growing stock on the global scale previously, with the displays at the World Relays further enhancing Ireland's reputation among the best.\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3484, \"end\": 3491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999959300112, \"rank\": 3.638917326227469e-09, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 3596, \"end\": 3603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999959300112, \"rank\": 3.638917326227469e-09, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the global scale\", \"